CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION longestPalindrome(s)  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF s  
        SET f TO a TWO DIMENSIONAL LIST of BOOLEAN TRUES with n ROWS and n COLUMNS  
        SET k TO zero  
        SET mx TO one  
        FOR i FROM n MINUS two DOWN TO zero  
            FOR j FROM i PLUS one TO n MINUS one  
                SET element at position i and position j of f TO FALSE  
                IF element at position i of s EQUALS element at position j of s  
                    SET element at position i and position j of f TO element at position i PLUS one and position j MINUS one of f  
                    IF element at position i and position j of f EQUALS TRUE AND mx LESS THAN j MINUS i PLUS one  
                        SET k TO i  
                        SET mx TO j MINUS i PLUS one  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN substring from position k TO position k PLUS mx MINUS one of s  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS
CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION uniquePaths(m n)  
        SET dp TO a two dimensional list with m rows and n columns where each element is set to one  
        FOR i FROM two TO m  
            FOR j FROM two TO n  
                SET element at position i of dp TO the list at position i of dp  
                SET element at position j of element at position i of dp TO the sum of the element at position i MINUS one of dp at position j AND the element at position i of dp at position j MINUS one  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN the element at position m MINUS one of dp at position n MINUS one  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION longestPalindrome(s)
        SET length AS THE COUNT OF s
        SET truth_matrix AS AN ARRAY (length) OF ARRAYS (length) FILLED WITH TRUE
        SET start_index AS 0
        SET max_length AS 1
        
        SET outer_index AS length MINUS 2
        WHILE outer_index IS GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO 0 DO
            SET inner_index AS outer_index PLUS 1
            WHILE inner_index IS LESS THAN length DO
                SET truth_matrix[outer_index][inner_index] AS FALSE
                
                IF NOT (s[outer_index] NOT EQUAL TO s[inner_index]) THEN
                    SET truth_matrix[outer_index][inner_index] AS truth_matrix[outer_index PLUS 1][inner_index MINUS 1]
                    
                    IF truth_matrix[outer_index][inner_index] IS TRUE THEN
                        IF (max_length LESS THAN (inner_index MINUS outer_index PLUS 1)) THEN
                            SET start_index AS outer_index
                            SET max_length AS (inner_index MINUS outer_index PLUS 1)
                        END IF
                    END IF
                END IF
                INCREMENT inner_index BY 1
            END WHILE
            DECREMENT outer_index BY 1
        END WHILE
        
        RETURN s SUBSTRING FROM start_index TO (start_index PLUS max_length MINUS 1)
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS
CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION myAtoi(s)  
        SET maxIntValue AS (2 ^ 31) - 1  
        SET minIntValue AS 0 - (2 ^ 31)  
        SET accumulatedNumber TO 0  
        SET position TO 0  
        SET lengthOfString TO LENGTH OF s  
        SET polarity TO 1  

        WHILE position < lengthOfString AND s[position] = ' '  
            position ← position + 1  
        END WHILE  

        IF position < lengthOfString THEN  
            SWITCH s[position]  
                CASE '-'  
                    polarity ← 0 - 1  
                    position ← position + 1  
                    BREAK  
                CASE '+'  
                    polarity ← 1  
                    position ← position + 1  
                    BREAK  
            END SWITCH  
        END IF  

        REPEAT UNTIL NOT (position < lengthOfString AND s[position] >= '0' AND s[position] <= '9')  
            SET currentChar TO s[position]  
            SET numericValue TO INTEGER VALUE OF currentChar  
            SET boundaryCheck TO maxIntValue - (numericValue DIV 10)  

            IF accumulatedNumber > boundaryCheck THEN  
                IF polarity = 1 THEN  
                    RETURN maxIntValue  
                ELSE  
                    RETURN minIntValue  
                END IF  
            END IF  

            accumulatedNumber ← (accumulatedNumber * 10) + numericValue  
            position ← position + 1  
        END REPEAT  

        RETURN polarity * accumulatedNumber  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

    FUNCTION canJump(list_of_numbers)

        FOR index FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF list_of_numbers MINUS one INCLUSIVE

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION multiply(num1 string, num2 string) RETURNS string
        IF num1 IS "0" OR num2 IS "0"
            RETURN "0"
        END IF

        DECLARE digits AS MAP from INT to INT
        DECLARE lengthSum AS INT = LENGTH(num1) + LENGTH(num2)
        FOR index IN RANGE(lengthSum)
            digits[index] = 0
        END FOR

        DECLARE reversed1 AS string = ""
        DECLARE reversed2 AS string = ""
        FOR p FROM LENGTH(num1) - 1 DOWNTO 0
            reversed1 = reversed1 + num1[p]
        END FOR
        FOR q FROM LENGTH(num2) - 1 DOWNTO 0
            reversed2 = reversed2 + num2[q]
        END FOR

        DECLARE function recursiveMul(i INT, j INT) RETURNS VOID
            IF i = LENGTH(reversed1)
                RETURN
            END IF
            IF j = LENGTH(reversed2)
                recursiveMul(i + 1, 0)
                RETURN
            END IF

            DECLARE valA AS INT = ASCII_CODE(reversed1[i]) - ASCII_CODE("0")
            DECLARE valB AS INT = ASCII_CODE(reversed2[j]) - ASCII_CODE("0")
            DECLARE product AS INT = valA * valB
            DECLARE baseIndex AS INT = i + j
            DECLARE nextIndex AS INT = baseIndex + 1
            DECLARE totalSum AS INT = product + digits[baseIndex]

            digits[baseIndex] = totalSum MOD 10
            digits[nextIndex] = digits[nextIndex] + (totalSum DIV 10)

            recursiveMul(i, j + 1)
        END FUNCTION

        CALL recursiveMul(0, 0)

        DECLARE output AS string = ""
        FOR key FROM lengthSum - 1 DOWNTO 0
            output = output + TO_STRING(digits[key])
        END FOR

        WHILE LENGTH(output) > 1 AND output[0] = "0"
            output = SUBSTRING(output, 1)
        END WHILE

        RETURN output
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION isMatch(s, p)
        SET x TO LENGTH(s)
        SET y TO LENGTH(p)
        SET dp TO []
        SET u TO 0
        WHILE u <= x
            SET tempList TO []
            SET v TO 0
            WHILE v <= y
                APPEND False TO tempList
                SET v TO v + 1
            END WHILE
            APPEND tempList TO dp
            SET u TO u + 1
        END WHILE

        SET dp[0][0] TO True

        PROCEDURE fillFirstRow(w)
            IF w > y THEN
                RETURN
            END IF
            IF p[w - 1] = '*'
                SET dp[0][w] TO dp[0][w - 1]
            END IF
            fillFirstRow(w + 1)
        END PROCEDURE

        CALL fillFirstRow(1)

        PROCEDURE processRow(i, j)
            IF i > x THEN
                RETURN
            END IF
            IF j > y THEN
                CALL processRow(i + 1, 1)
                RETURN
            END IF

            SWITCH TRUE
                CASE (p[j - 1] = '*')
                    SET dp[i][j] TO dp[i - 1][j] OR dp[i][j - 1]
                BREAK

                CASE (p[j - 1] = '?' OR s[i - 1] = p[j - 1])
                    SET dp[i][j] TO dp[i - 1][j - 1]
                BREAK

                DEFAULT
                    // dp[i][j] remains False implicitly
                BREAK
            END SWITCH

            processRow(i, j + 1)
        END PROCEDURE

        CALL processRow(1, 1)

        RETURN dp[x][y]
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

    FUNCTION combine WITH PARAMETERS n k
        SET outcome TO []
        FUNCTION backtrack WITH PARAMETERS pos seq
            WHILE pos NOT EQUAL TO n + 1
                APPEND pos TO seq
                IF LENGTH seq EQUALS k THEN
                    APPEND COPY OF seq TO outcome
                ELSE

                SET pos TO pos + 1
